cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper discusses privacy concerns related to the transfer of personal data generated by smart devices to centralized computational systems for analysis. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a computational framework for measuring privacy-utility trade-offs, which involves machine learning techniques and optimization algorithms, indicating a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the role of incentives in data sharing, which could be related to cybernetics (cs.CY).
